14. Longest Common Prefix
Write a function to find the longest common prefix string amongst an array of strings.

If there is no common prefix, return an empty string "".

Example 1:

Input: strs = ["flower","flow","flight"]
Output: "fl"
Example 2:

Input: strs = ["dog","racecar","car"]
Output: ""
Explanation: There is no common prefix among the input strings.
 

Constraints:

1 <= strs.length <= 200
0 <= strs[i].length <= 200
strs[i] consists of only lowercase English letters if it is non-empty.

Approach:
1.Assume first element is the common prefix
2.Now iterate through array elements and check for the prefix
3.Check if strs[i] starts with the prefix [index Of return 0 only if prefix is at very beginning]
    If prefix becomes empty then return ""
            

Solution:
class Solution {
    public String longestCommonPrefix(String[] strs) {
        if(strs == null || strs.length==0) return "";
       //Assume first element is the common prefix
       String prefix=strs[0];

       //Now iterate through array elements and check for the prefix
       for(int i=1;i<strs.length;i++){
        //Check if strs[i] starts with the prefix
        //index Of return 0 only if prefix is at very beginning
        while(strs[i].indexOf(prefix) != 0){
            prefix=prefix.substring(0,prefix.length()-1);

            //If prefix becomes empty then return ""
            if(prefix.isEmpty()){
                return "";
            }
        }
       }
       return prefix;
    }
}
